22 pages from the web. It has a memory cache for these objects.

25#pragma once
26
27#include "SecurityOriginHash.h"
28#include "Timer.h"
29#include <pal/SessionID.h>
30#include <wtf/Forward.h>
31#include <wtf/Function.h>
32#include <wtf/HashMap.h>
33#include <wtf/HashSet.h>
34#include <wtf/ListHashSet.h>
35#include <wtf/Noncopyable.h>
36#include <wtf/Vector.h>
37#include <wtf/text/StringHash.h>
38#include <wtf/text/WTFString.h>

40namespace WebCore {
41
42class CachedResource;
43class CookieJar;
44class ResourceRequest;
45class ResourceResponse;
46class ScriptExecutionContext;
47class SecurityOrigin;
48
49// This cache holds subresources used by Web pages: images, scripts, stylesheets, etc.
50
51// The cache keeps a flexible but bounded window of dead resources that grows/shrinks
52// depending on the live resource load. Here's an example of cache growth over time,
53// with a min dead resource capacity of 25% and a max dead resource capacity of 50%:
54
55// |-----| Dead: -
56// |----------| Live: +
57// --|----------| Cache boundary: | (objects outside this mark have been evicted)
58// --|----------++++++++++|
59// -------|-----+++++++++++++++|
60// -------|-----+++++++++++++++|+++++
61
62class MemoryCache {
63 WTF_MAKE_NONCOPYABLE(MemoryCache); WTF_MAKE_FAST_ALLOCATED;
64 friend NeverDestroyed<MemoryCache>;
65 friend class Internals;
66public:
67 struct TypeStatistic {
68 int count;
69 int size;
70 int liveSize;
71 int decodedSize;
72
73 TypeStatistic()
74 : count(0)
75 , size(0)
76 , liveSize(0)
77 , decodedSize(0)
78 {
79 }
80
81 void addResource(CachedResource&);
82 };
83
84 struct Statistics {
85 TypeStatistic images;
86 TypeStatistic cssStyleSheets;
87 TypeStatistic scripts;
88 TypeStatistic xslStyleSheets;
89 TypeStatistic fonts;
90 };
91
92 WEBCORE_EXPORT static MemoryCache& singleton();
93
94 WEBCORE_EXPORT CachedResource* resourceForRequest(const ResourceRequest&, PAL::SessionID);
95
96 bool add(CachedResource&);
97 void remove(CachedResource&);
98
99 static bool shouldRemoveFragmentIdentifier(const URL&);
100 static URL removeFragmentIdentifierIfNeeded(const URL&);
101
102 void revalidationSucceeded(CachedResource& revalidatingResource, const ResourceResponse&);
103 void revalidationFailed(CachedResource& revalidatingResource);
104
105 void forEachResource(const WTF::Function<void(CachedResource&)>&);
106 void forEachSessionResource(PAL::SessionID, const WTF::Function<void(CachedResource&)>&);
107 WEBCORE_EXPORT void destroyDecodedDataForAllImages();
108
109 // Sets the cache's memory capacities, in bytes. These will hold only approximately,
110 // since the decoded cost of resources like scripts and stylesheets is not known.
111 // - minDeadBytes: The maximum number of bytes that dead resources should consume when the cache is under pressure.
112 // - maxDeadBytes: The maximum number of bytes that dead resources should consume when the cache is not under pressure.
113 // - totalBytes: The maximum number of bytes that the cache should consume overall.
114 WEBCORE_EXPORT void setCapacities(unsigned minDeadBytes, unsigned maxDeadBytes, unsigned totalBytes);
115
116 // Turn the cache on and off. Disabling the cache will remove all resources from the cache. They may
117 // still live on if they are referenced by some Web page though.
118 WEBCORE_EXPORT void setDisabled(bool);
119 bool disabled() const { return m_disabled; }
120
121 WEBCORE_EXPORT void evictResources();
122 WEBCORE_EXPORT void evictResources(PAL::SessionID);
123
124 void prune();
125 void pruneSoon();
126 unsigned size() const { return m_liveSize + m_deadSize; }
127
128 void setDeadDecodedDataDeletionInterval(Seconds interval) { m_deadDecodedDataDeletionInterval = interval; }
129 Seconds deadDecodedDataDeletionInterval() const { return m_deadDecodedDataDeletionInterval; }
130
131 // Calls to put the cached resource into and out of LRU lists.
132 void insertInLRUList(CachedResource&);
133 void removeFromLRUList(CachedResource&);
134
135 // Called to adjust the cache totals when a resource changes size.
136 void adjustSize(bool live, long long delta);
137
138 // Track decoded resources that are in the cache and referenced by a Web page.
139 void insertInLiveDecodedResourcesList(CachedResource&);
140 void removeFromLiveDecodedResourcesList(CachedResource&);
141
142 void addToLiveResourcesSize(CachedResource&);
143 void removeFromLiveResourcesSize(CachedResource&);
144
145 static void removeRequestFromSessionCaches(ScriptExecutionContext&, const ResourceRequest&);
146
147 // Function to collect cache statistics for the caches window in the Safari Debug menu.
148 WEBCORE_EXPORT Statistics getStatistics();
149
150 void resourceAccessed(CachedResource&);
151 bool inLiveDecodedResourcesList(CachedResource& resource) const { return m_liveDecodedResources.contains(&resource); }
152
153 typedef HashSet<RefPtr<SecurityOrigin>> SecurityOriginSet;
154 WEBCORE_EXPORT void removeResourcesWithOrigin(SecurityOrigin&);
155 WEBCORE_EXPORT void removeResourcesWithOrigins(PAL::SessionID, const HashSet<RefPtr<SecurityOrigin>>&);
156 WEBCORE_EXPORT void getOriginsWithCache(SecurityOriginSet& origins);
157 WEBCORE_EXPORT HashSet<RefPtr<SecurityOrigin>> originsWithCache(PAL::SessionID) const;
158
159 // pruneDead*() - Flush decoded and encoded data from resources not referenced by Web pages.
160 // pruneLive*() - Flush decoded data from resources still referenced by Web pages.
161 WEBCORE_EXPORT void pruneDeadResources(); // Automatically decide how much to prune.
162 WEBCORE_EXPORT void pruneLiveResources(bool shouldDestroyDecodedDataForAllLiveResources = false);
163
164 WEBCORE_EXPORT void pruneDeadResourcesToSize(unsigned targetSize);
165 WEBCORE_EXPORT void pruneLiveResourcesToSize(unsigned targetSize, bool shouldDestroyDecodedDataForAllLiveResources = false);
166
167private:
168 typedef HashMap<std::pair<URL, String /* partitionName */>, CachedResource*> CachedResourceMap;
169 typedef ListHashSet<CachedResource*> LRUList;
170
171 MemoryCache();
172 ~MemoryCache(); // Not implemented to make sure nobody accidentally calls delete -- WebCore does not delete singletons.
173
174 LRUList& lruListFor(CachedResource&);
175
176 void dumpStats();
177 void dumpLRULists(bool includeLive) const;
178
179 unsigned liveCapacity() const;
180 unsigned deadCapacity() const;
181 bool needsPruning() const;
182
183 CachedResource* resourceForRequestImpl(const ResourceRequest&, CachedResourceMap&);
184
185 CachedResourceMap& ensureSessionResourceMap(PAL::SessionID);
186 CachedResourceMap* sessionResourceMap(PAL::SessionID) const;
187
188 bool m_disabled { false };
189 bool m_inPruneResources { false };
190
191 unsigned m_capacity;
192 unsigned m_minDeadCapacity { 0 };
193 unsigned m_maxDeadCapacity;
194 Seconds m_deadDecodedDataDeletionInterval;
195
196 unsigned m_liveSize { 0 }; // The number of bytes currently consumed by "live" resources in the cache.
197 unsigned m_deadSize { 0 }; // The number of bytes currently consumed by "dead" resources in the cache.
198
199 // Size-adjusted and popularity-aware LRU list collection for cache objects. This collection can hold
200 // more resources than the cached resource map, since it can also hold "stale" multiple versions of objects that are
201 // waiting to die when the clients referencing them go away.
202 Vector<std::unique_ptr<LRUList>, 32> m_allResources;
203
204 // List just for live resources with decoded data. Access to this list is based off of painting the resource.
205 LRUList m_liveDecodedResources;
206
207 // A URL-based map of all resources that are in the cache (including the freshest version of objects that are currently being
208 // referenced by a Web page).
209 typedef HashMap<PAL::SessionID, std::unique_ptr<CachedResourceMap>> SessionCachedResourceMap;
210 SessionCachedResourceMap m_sessionResources;
211
212 Timer m_pruneTimer;
213};
214
215} // namespace WebCore
